{"type":"message","id":"62ccd00a","parentId":"ace7b56f","timestamp":"2026-05-06T22:15:41.128Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Wed 2026-05-06 17:15 CDT] I am going to give you a deployment protocol for my UDD backend in two parts. Do not execute anything yet. Just reply \"Acknowledged\" after you read this first half.\n\n## SYSTEM CONTEXT: IDENTITY & ROLE\nYou are **LineintheLinux**, my Linux server manager. Your primary role is managing two main spaces on my Legion server: my personal dev stack and my apps backend. \n\nYour mandate is to keep these spaces cleanly separated. You are professional, precise, and strictly enforce architectural boundaries. You do not allow volatile development tools to bleed into production environments. \n\nYour first task in this role is to deploy the backend for my app, UDD (U-Did-Dat). \n\n---\n\n## DEPLOYMENT PROTOCOL: UDD-WEB (PART 1)\n\n### 0. Golden rule\nThe Legion host already runs a production stack. UDD is a **new tenant** on that host. It adds exactly one container (`udd-web`) and one Caddyfile site block. Nothing else changes.\n\nIf you discover that a previous agent run already modified `docker-compose.yml`, the Caddyfile, or any running container in a way not listed here, **stop and report** — do not attempt to reconcile silently.\n\n---\n\n### 1. Pre-flight audit (read-only — change nothing)\nRun all of the following. Capture every output line in the bring-back report.\n\n```bash\n# 1.1 Host identity\nhostname && uname -r && docker --version && docker compose version\n\n# 1.2 Running containers — names, image, status, ports\ndocker ps --format 'table {{.Names}}\\t{{.Image}}\\t{{.Status}}\\t{{.Ports}}'\n\n# 1.3 All Docker networks\ndocker network ls\n\n# 1.4 Confirm server_internal exists and which containers are on it\ndocker network inspect server_internal --format \\\n  '{{range .Containers}}{{.Name}} {{end}}' 2>/dev/null || echo \"MISSING: server_internal\"\n\n# 1.5 Existing compose stack\ncat /home/asher/server/docker-compose.yml\n\n# 1.6 Current Caddyfile\ncat /home/asher/server/caddy/Caddyfile\n\n# 1.7 Postgres roles and databases (read-only query)\ndocker exec postgres psql -U hermes -c \"\\du\" -c \"\\l\"\n\n# 1.8 udd_prod and udd_app already exist? (from Phase 0)\ndocker exec postgres psql -U hermes -c \\\n  \"SELECT rolname FROM pg_roles WHERE rolname='udd_app';\" \\\n  -c \"SELECT datname FROM pg_database WHERE datname='udd_prod';\"\n\n# 1.9 Check for any prior udd-web artifacts\ndocker ps -a --filter name=udd-web\nls /srv/udd/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"MISSING: /srv/udd\"\ndocker images | grep udd-web || echo \"no udd-web image\"\n\n# 1.10 Forgejo registry reachability\ndocker login git.asherlewis.online 2>&1 | head -5 || echo \"registry login needed\"\n\n# 1.11 Confirm forgejo is using host port 3000 (collision check)\ndocker port forgejo 2>/dev/null || docker inspect forgejo --format '{{.HostConfig.PortBindings}}'\n\n# 1.12 Check if udd_app password file exists from Phase 0\nls -la /home/asher/.hermes/secrets/udd-web-postgres-udd_prod-password.txt 2>/dev/null \\\n  || echo \"MISSING: password file\""}],"timestamp":1778105741126}}
{"type":"message","id":"4a7a93e9","parentId":"62ccd00a","timestamp":"2026-05-06T22:15:55.542Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking me to just acknowledge that I've read PART 1 of the deployment protocol, not to execute anything yet. They want me to reply \"Acknowledged\" after reading the first half.\n\nI need to check if I have already read it - yes, I can see it in the conversation history. The user posted it and is asking for acknowledgment.\n\nSo I should simply reply \"Acknowledged\" without executing any commands or making changes.\n\nBut wait, I should check if there's a bootstrap still pending? Looking at the conversation, we did bootstrap earlier - I updated IDENTITY.md and USER.md. The BOOTSTRAP.md file was deleted? Actually, I never deleted it. Let me check if BOOTSTRAP.md still exists.\n\nActually, looking back at the conversation: after I responded to the bootstrap prompt, the user gave me the SYSTEM CONTEXT about being LineintheLinux and the deployment protocol. That suggests the bootstrap is complete and we're now in the main task.\n\nThe user said: \"Do not execute anything yet. Just reply 'Acknowledged' after you read this first half.\"\n\nSo I should just reply with \"Acknowledged\".\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Acknowledged"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":21298,"output":246,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21544,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778105741129,"responseId":"chatcmpl-88196912047215b8"}}
