{"type":"message","id":"2d74c7d4","parentId":"85ceae9d","timestamp":"2026-05-06T22:46:53.156Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Wed 2026-05-06 17:46 CDT] Here is the second half of the deployment protocol. You may now begin the pre-flight audit (Step 1) and execute the protocol.\n\n## DEPLOYMENT PROTOCOL: UDD-WEB (PART 2)\n\n### 7. Add Caddyfile site block\nAppend one site block; do not touch any existing blocks.\n\n```bash\n# 7.1 Verify the existing Caddyfile does NOT already have a udd block\ngrep -n 'udd\\.' /home/asher/server/caddy/Caddyfile \\\n  && echo \"WARNING: existing udd block found — review before appending\" \\\n  || echo \"clean — no udd block yet\"\n\n# 7.2 Append the site block\nsudo tee -a /home/asher/server/caddy/Caddyfile > /dev/null <<'CADDYEOF'\n\nudd.asherlewis.online {\n    encode zstd gzip\n    reverse_proxy udd-web:3000\n\n    header_up X-Forwarded-Proto {scheme}\n}\nCADDYEOF\n\n# 7.3 Reload Caddy in-place\ndocker exec caddy caddy reload --config /etc/caddy/Caddyfile --adapter caddyfile\n\n# 7.4 Verify reload succeeded\necho \"Caddy reload exit: $?\"\ndocker logs --tail=10 caddy"}],"timestamp":1778107613155}}
