{"type":"message","id":"8b0bda2c","parentId":"ab3fa4db","timestamp":"2026-05-06T23:09:44.648Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-a68f8f23402b9244","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Postgres provisioning for udd-web on Legion\nGenerated: 2026-05-04T06:41:53.537223+00:00\n## Verdict\nPROVISIONED\n\nPasswords are redacted as `***`. The generated `udd_app` password is not printed in this bring-back.\nThe generated password was saved for separate local handoff at `/home/asher/.hermes/secrets/udd-web-postgres-udd_prod-password.txt` with mode 600; file content is not shown.\n\n## Phase A — Pre-flight (read-only)\n\n### A1 Container running\nCommand:\n```bash\ndocker ps --filter name=^/postgres$ --format 'table {{.Names}}\t{{.Image}}\t{{.Status}}\t{{.Ports}}'\n```\nExit code: 0\nOutput:\n```text\nNAMES      IMAGE         STATUS        PORTS\npostgres   postgres:16   Up 25 hours   5432/tcp\n```\n\n### A2 Server version + current roles + databases\nCommand:\n```bash\ndocker exec postgres psql -U hermes -d postgres -v ON_ERROR_STOP=1 -P pager=off -c 'SELECT version();' -c 'SELECT rolname, rolsuper, rolcreatedb, rolcreaterole, rolcanlogin FROM pg_roles ORDER BY rolname;' -c 'SELECT datname, pg_get_userbyid(datdba) AS owner, pg_encoding_to_char(encoding) AS encoding FROM pg_database ORDER BY datname;'\n```\nExit code: 0\nOutput:\n```text\nversion                                                        \n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n PostgreSQL 16.13 (Debian 16.13-1.pgdg13+1) on x86_64-pc-linux-gnu, compiled by gcc (Debian 14.2.0-19) 14.2.0, 64-bit\n(1 row)\n\n           rolname           | rolsuper | rolcreatedb | rolcreaterole | rolcanlogin \n-----------------------------+----------+-------------+---------------+-------------\n hermes                      | t        | t           | t             | t\n pg_checkpoint               | f        | f           | f             | f\n pg_create_subscription      | f        | f           | f             | f\n pg_database_owner           | f        | f           | f             | f\n pg_execute_server_program   | f        | f           | f             | f\n pg_monitor                  | f        | f           | f             | f\n pg_read_all_data            | f        | f           | f             | f\n pg_read_all_settings        | f        | f           | f             | f\n pg_read_all_stats           | f        | f           | f             | f\n pg_read_server_files        | f        | f           | f             | f\n pg_signal_backend           | f        | f           | f             | f\n pg_stat_scan_tables         | f        | f           | f             | f\n pg_use_reserved_connections | f        | f           | f             | f\n pg_write_all_data           | f        | f           | f             | f\n pg_write_server_files       | f        | f           | f             | f\n(15 rows)\n\n  datname  | owner  | encoding \n-----------+--------+----------\n forgejo   | hermes | UTF8\n postgres  | hermes | UTF8\n template0 | hermes | UTF8\n template1 | hermes | UTF8\n(4 rows)\n```\n\n### A3 Confirm Forgejo database owner and baseline count\nCommand:\n```bash\ndocker exec postgres psql -U hermes -d postgres -v ON_ERROR_STOP=1 -P pager=off -c 'SELECT datname, pg_get_userbyid(datdba) AS owner FROM pg_database WHERE datname = '\"'\"'forgejo'\"'\"';' && docker exec postgres psql -U hermes -d forgejo -v ON_ERROR_STOP=1 -P pager=off -c 'SELECT count(*) AS forgejo_public_table_count FROM information_schema.tables WHERE table_schema = '\"'\"'public'\"'\"';'\n```\nExit code: 0\nOutput:\n```text\ndatname | owner  \n---------+--------\n forgejo | hermes\n(1 row)\n\n forgejo_public_table_count \n----------------------------\n                        122\n(1 row)\n```\n\n### A4 Confirm udd_app role absent\nCommand:\n```bash\ndocker exec postgres psql -U hermes -d postgres -v ON_ERROR_STOP=1 -P pager=off -c 'SELECT rolname FROM pg_roles WHERE rolname = '\"'\"'udd_app'\"'\"';'\n```\nExit code: 0\nOutput:\n```text\nrolname \n---------\n(0 rows)\n```\n\n### A4 Confirm udd_prod database absent\nCommand:\n```bash\ndocker exec postgres psql -U hermes -d postgres -v ON_ERROR_STOP=1 -P pager=off -c 'SELECT datname FROM pg_database WHERE datname = '\"'\"'udd_prod'\"'\"';'\n```\nExit code: 0\nOutput:\n```text\ndatname \n---------\n(0 rows)\n```\n\n## Phase B — Decision\n\n### B1 Postgres reachable smoke test\nCommand:\n```bash\ndocker exec postgres psql -U hermes -d postgres -v ON_ERROR_STOP=1 -P pager=off -c 'SELECT current_database() AS db, current_user AS db_user, 1 AS reachable;'\n```\nExit code: 0\nOutput:\n```text\ndb    | db_user | reachable \n----------+---------+-----------\n postgres | hermes  |         1\n(1 row)\n```\n\n### B2 Confirm hermes can create role/database\nCommand:\n```bash\ndocker exec postgres psql -U hermes -d postgres -v ON_ERROR_STOP=1 -P pager=off -c 'SELECT current_user AS db_user, rolsuper, rolcreatedb, rolcreaterole FROM pg_roles WHERE rolname = current_user;'\n```\nExit code: 0\nOutput:\n```text\ndb_user | rolsuper | rolcreatedb | rolcreaterole \n---------+----------+-------------+---------------\n hermes  | t        | t           | t\n(1 row)\n```\n\n### B3 Confirm `udd_app` and `udd_prod` absent\n`udd_app` absent: True. `udd_prod` absent: True. Citations: Phase A A4 outputs.\n\n### B4 Generate strong password for `udd_app` locally\nCommand shape:\n```bash\nUDD_DB_PASSWORD=\"$(openssl rand -base64 36 | tr -d \"\\n\")\"; export UDD_DB_PASSWORD\n```\nExit code: 0\nOutput:\n```text\n[password generated; value redacted as ***]\n```\n\n### B5 Final decision\nPROCEED\n- Postgres running/reachable, `hermes` has required privileges, `udd_app` and `udd_prod` were absent, Forgejo baseline was captured, and password was generated.\n\n## Phase C — Apply\n\n### C1 Create udd_app role\nCommand shape:\n```bash\ndocker exec postgres psql -U hermes -d postgres -v ON_ERROR_STOP=1 -P pager=off -c 'CREATE ROLE udd_app WITH LOGIN PASSWORD '***'\"'***'\"'\"';'\n```\nExit code: 0\nOutput:\n```text\nCREATE ROLE\n```\n\n### C2 Create udd_prod database owned by udd_app\nCommand shape:\n```bash\ndocker exec postgres psql -U hermes -d postgres -v ON_ERROR_STOP=1 -P pager=off -c 'CREATE DATABASE udd_prod OWNER udd_app;'\n```\nExit code: 0\nOutput:\n```text\nCREATE DATABASE\n```\n\n### C3 Lock down public schema on udd_prod\nCommand shape:\n```bash\ndocker exec postgres psql -U hermes -d udd_prod -v ON_ERROR_STOP=1 -P pager=off -c 'REVOKE ALL ON SCHEMA public FROM PUBLIC; ALTER SCHEMA public OWNER TO udd_app; GRANT ALL ON SCHEMA public TO udd_app;'\n```\nExit code: 0\nOutput:\n```text\nREVOKE\nALTER SCHEMA\nGRANT\n```\n\n### C4 Verify udd_app connection inside docker network\nCommand shape:\n```bash\ndocker exec postgres sh -lc 'PGPASSWORD=*** psql -h postgres -U udd_app -d udd_prod -v ON_ERROR_STOP=1 -P pager=off -c '\"'\"'SELECT current_database() AS db, current_user AS db_user, current_schema() AS schema, 1 AS ok; CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS provisioning_smoke_test(id integer PRIMARY KEY); DROP TABLE provisioning_smoke_test;'\"'\"''\n```\nExit code: 0\nOutput:\n```text\ndb    | db_user | schema | ok \n----------+---------+--------+----\n udd_prod | udd_app | public |  1\n(1 row)\n\nCREATE TABLE\nDROP TABLE\n```\n\n### C5 Re-confirm Forgejo baseline count after apply\nCommand shape:\n```bash\ndocker exec postgres psql -U hermes -d forgejo -v ON_ERROR_STOP=1 -P pager=off -c 'SELECT count(*) AS forgejo_public_table_count FROM information_schema.tables WHERE table_schema = '\"'\"'public'\"'\"';'\n```\nExit code: 0\nOutput:\n```text\nforgejo_public_table_count \n----------------------------\n                        122\n(1 row)\n```\n\n### C6 Secret handoff file metadata (content not shown)\nCommand shape:\n```bash\nstat -c '%n owner=%U group=%G mode=%a bytes=%s' /home/asher/.hermes/secrets/udd-web-postgres-udd_prod-password.txt\n```\nExit code: 0\nOutput:\n```text\n/home/asher/.hermes/secrets/udd-web-postgres-udd_prod-password.txt owner=asher group=asher mode=600 bytes=49\n```\n\nForgejo public table-count baseline: `122`. After apply: `122`. Match: True.\n\n## Scope confirmation\n- No compose file edits were made by this task.\n- No containers were restarted by this task.\n- No new containers were created by this task.\n- Postgres changes were limited to creating role `udd_app`, creating database `udd_prod`, and locking down schema privileges inside `udd_prod`.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778108984648}}
