{"type":"message","id":"7386bd5c","parentId":"423a5b73","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:13:25.699Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to check if Caddy v2 uses header_up or header. According to Caddy docs, header_up is a subdirective of reverse_proxy. Actually, for setting headers on upstream requests, you can use header_up inside reverse_proxy block. But the syntax is:\n\nreverse_proxy upstream {\n    header_up X-Forwarded-Proto {scheme}\n}\n\nSo we need to move header inside reverse_proxy. Let's adjust.\n\nWe'll edit the Caddyfile to put header_up inside reverse_proxy.\n\nLet's do that.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-b322b3410e398b6b","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat > /tmp/newblock <<'EOF'\nudd.asherlewis.online {\n    encode zstd gzip\n    reverse_proxy udd-web:3000 {\n        header_up X-Forwarded-Proto {scheme}\n    }\n}\nEOF"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":51040,"output":186,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51226,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778116397770,"responseId":"chatcmpl-9a8fa92aedd06020"}}
