ome/asher/server/caddy/Caddyfile.bak2\n   cat > /home/asher/server/caddy/Caddyfile <<'EOF'\ngit.asherlewis.online {\n    reverse_proxy forgejo:3000\n}\n\nqdrant.asherlewis.online {\n    reverse_proxy qdrant:6333\n}\n\nmcp.asherlewis.online {\n    reverse_proxy localhost:8811\n}\n\nudd.asherlewis.online {\n    encode zstd gzip\n    reverse_proxy udd-web:3000 {\n        header_up X-Forwarded-Proto {scheme}\n    }\n}\nEOF\n\n But note: we already have the file. Let's just replace the udd block.\n\n Alternatively, let's use the container's caddy to format the file and then reload.\n\n However, we are in a heartbeat and must be efficient.\n\n Let's try to validate the file in the container:\n\n   docker exec caddy caddy validate --config /etc/caddy/Caddyfile --adapter caddyfile\n\n But we are getting the error.\n\n Let's check the file in the container:\n\n   docker exec caddy cat /etc/caddy/Caddyfile\n\n And compare with the host.\n\n Since we are binding the host file, they should be the same.\n\n Let's do that.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-b80c9aa9a9a1816d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker exec caddy cat /etc/caddy/Caddyfile"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":52950,"output":720,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53670,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778116572066,"responseId":"chatcmpl-b8f9f3d7987aa05f"}}
