m host directories owned by asher:asher. So we'll create /srv/udd owned by asher:asher.\n\nBut the protocol said \"sudo mkdir -p /srv/udd && sudo chown 70:70 /srv/udd\". That suggests they expect the container to run as uid 70. We'll do that with elevated privileges if needed. However we cannot use sudo because we don't have TTY. We can try to use chown with elevated flag? The elevated tool is not available. We'll need to see if we can chown without sudo; we are asher, we can chown if we own the directory. We'll create the directory as asher, then chown to 70:70 only if we have permission (we might not). Let's first create the directory and see if we can chown.\n\nWe'll attempt to chown; if permission denied, we'll note and maybe run as elevated? But elevated is not available. We'll see.\n\nLet's start by reading the password file to know the password.\n\nThen we'll write the docker-compose snippet.\n\nWe'll also need to check if there is a docker-compose.yml.override or something.\n\nLet's do these steps now.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-b4083f03372a9370","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/asher/.hermes/secrets/udd-web-postgres-udd_prod-password.txt"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":66140,"output":1680,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67820,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778118522853,"responseId":"chatcmpl-8e3935f49f1651ff"}}
