t.\n\n- Then output a message that the image pull failed and we cannot proceed without the image.\n\nWe'll also need to check if there is a Dockerfile in the udd-web directory that we can use to build locally? But the protocol says \"nothing else changes\". Building an image would be a change? Actually building an image locally and loading it into docker is still a change (creates an image). However the protocol says \"If you discover that a previous agent run already modified docker-compose.yml, the Caddyfile, or any running container in a way not listed here, stop and report\". It doesn't say we cannot build an image if missing, but the golden rule says UDD is a new tenant adding exactly one container and one Caddyfile site block. It doesn't forbid building the image if it's not in the registry, but the instruction says to pull the image. If the image is not there, we should stop and report.\n\nLet's report.\n\nWe'll now finish the pre-flight audit and then output the failure.\n\nLet's write the rest of the pre-flight audit (we already have up to 1.12). We'll add a separator and then note the image pull failure.\n\nWe'll also need to output the pre-flight audit as part of the bring-back report? The protocol says \"Capture every output line in the bring-back report.\" So we should output the audit.\n\nWe'll do:\n\n- Write the audit to a file and then cat it.\n\n- Then report the image pull failure.\n\nLet's do that now.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-8c9d593590afdb15","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/asher && {\n  echo \"=== 1.1 Host identity ===\"\n  hostname && uname -r && docker --version && docker compose version\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"=== 1.2 Running containers ===\"\n  docker ps --format 'table {{.Names}}\\t{{.Image}}\\t{{.Status}}\\t{{.Ports}}'\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"=== 1.3 All Docker networks ===\"\n  docker network ls\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"=== 1.4 Confirm server_internal exists and which containers are on it ===\"\n  docker network inspect server_internal --format '{{range .Containers}}{{.Name}} {{end}}' 2>/dev/null || echo \"MISSING: server_internal\"\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"=== 1.5 Existing compose stack ===\"\n  cat /home/asher/server/docker-compose.yml\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"=== 1.6 Current Caddyfile ===\"\n  cat /home/asher/server/caddy/Caddyfile\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"=== 1.7 Postgres roles and databases (read-only query) ===\"\n  docker exec postgres psql -U hermes -d forgejo -c \"\\du\" -c \"\\l\" 2>&1\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"=== 1.8 udd_prod and udd_app already exist? (from Phase 0) ===\"\n  docker exec postgres psql -U hermes -d forgejo -c \"SELECT rolname FROM pg_roles WHERE rolname='udd_app';\" -c \"SELECT datname FROM pg_database WHERE datname='udd_prod';\" 2>&1\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"=== 1.9 Check for any prior udd-web artifacts ===\"\n  docker ps -a --filter name=udd-web\n  ls -la /srv/udd/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"MISSING: /srv/udd\"\n  docker images | grep udd-web || echo \"no udd-web image\"\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"=== 1.10 Forgejo registry reachability ===\"\n  docker login git.asherlewis.online 2>&1 | head -5\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"=== 1.11 Confirm forgejo is using host port 3000 (collision check) ===\"\n  docker port forgejo 2>/dev/null || docker inspect forgejo --format '{{.HostConfig.PortBindings}}'\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"=== 1.12 Check if udd_app password file exists from Phase 0 ===\"\n  ls -la /home/asher/.hermes/secrets/udd-web-postgres-udd_prod-password.txt 2>/dev/null || echo \"MISSING: password file\"\n} > /home/asher/.openclaw/workspace/udd-web-deployment/preflight-audit.md 2>&1"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":67550,"output":1371,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68921,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778121820962,"responseId":"chatcmpl-8157a84bde736a80"}}
